  "prompt": "Do employees at Spark Energy have a good work-life balance? Does this differ across positions and departments?",
  "response": "While I don't have access to real-time employee reviews or internal data specific to Spark Energy, employee experiences regarding work-life balance can vary significantly based on several factors, including specific roles, departments, and management styles. \n\nTo get an accurate sense of the work-life balance at Spark Energy, it would be beneficial to look at employee reviews on job sites like Glassdoor or Indeed. These reviews often provide insights into how employees perceive their workload, flexibility, and overall job satisfaction. Additionally, reaching out to current or former employees on professional networking platforms like LinkedIn can provide valuable first-hand perspectives.\n\nIn general, positions that require more client-facing or time-sensitive work (like sales or customer service) may often report more demanding schedules compared to roles in IT, finance, or administration, which may offer more flexibility. Company culture and management practices play essential roles in shaping work-life balance as well. \n\nFor the most accurate and current information, consider checking recent reviews and employee feedback specifically related to Spark Energy.",
